Name: Lady Finger (Bhindi)
Detailed_Description: A highly versatile vegetable in the Indian cuisine, Lady Finger can be sliced or chopped or can be paired with other vegetables for an exquisite taste. Toss in some green chillies or onions for a flavourful, wholesome main course dish.

Name: Potato (Aloo)
Detailed_Description: Potato is a starchy vegetable that is widely used in many recipes. Due to its bland taste, peeled potatoes can be mixed with a number of vegetables. Potatoes are also used in making chips and snacks.

Name: Lettuce Mix
Detailed_Description: Protect Your Heart. Lettuce contains two key nutrients in significant levels that help to protect the heart muscle: folate and fiber. High levels of folate have been shown to assist in the prevention of stroke and cardiovascular disease.

Name: Orange Carrot (Gajar)
Detailed_Description: Enjoy the sweet, crisp flavor of Orange Carrots. Packed with beta-carotene, vitamins, and antioxidants, they promote eye health and boost immunity. Perfect for snacking, salads, and cooking, these carrots add a nutritious touch to your meals.

Name: Fresh Rosemary
Detailed_Description: Rosemary is a fragrant herb used to flavor roasted meats and savory dishes like vegetables and potatoes. Enjoy its distinct pine-like aroma in a variety of recipes.

Name: English Cucumber (Kheera)
Detailed_Description: Long and narrow, English Cucumber has small seeds but is confused with being seedless. It helps soothe the tired eyes due to its cleansing and refreshing properties. Excellent for salad, cooking and other summer coolers, English Cucumber refreshes and hydrates your body.

Name: Green Capsicum 500 g (Shimla Mirch)
Detailed_Description: Capsicum has a wonderful bell shape, thick and brittle skin with glossy outer cover and a fleshy texture. Slightly less ripe, Capsicum has a vibrant colour and flavour. A staple in salads, it can be cooked or grilled -either ways it adds zing to any recipe.

Name: French Beans - 250 g
Detailed_Description: French beans, also known as green beans or string beans, are slender, crisp, and vibrant green pods that are popular in culinary dishes around the world.

Name: Arvi
Detailed_Description: Arbi, also known as taro root or colocasia, is a starchy tuber used in many cuisines. It has a mild flavor and creamy texture when cooked, often used in curries, stir-fries, and snacks. Incorporate arbi into your cooking for its unique taste and versatility!

Name: Bitter Gourd (Karela)
Detailed_Description: Bitter Gourd is often used in making dry vegetable curries. It is also taken in the form of juice as it contains many antioxidants and essential vitamins.

Name: Onion (Pyaz)
Detailed_Description: Onion is a staple in India and are commonly chopped and used as an ingredient in various hearty warm dishes. They are versatile and can be baked, boiled, braised, grilled, fried, roasted, sautéed, or eaten raw in salads.

Name: Desi Tomato (Tamaatar)
Detailed_Description: Tomatoes are a significant source of umami flavor.The tomato is consumed in diverse ways, raw or cooked, in many dishes, sauces, salads, and drinks. While tomatoes are fruits—botanically classified as berries—they are commonly used culinarily as a vegetable ingredient or side dish.

Name: Beetroot (Chukandar)
Detailed_Description: Beetroot pulp has a sweet taste and it is usually of a dark crimson red colour with purple tinges. The rich flesh of this vegetable is naturally sweet and nutritious, and adds its own touch to dishes ranging from Salads to Soups.

Name: Green Lettuce
Detailed_Description: Lettuce is a crisp, leafy green vegetable commonly used in salads and sandwiches. It has a mild flavor and adds freshness and texture to dishes. Enjoy lettuce raw in salads or as a wrap for sandwiches for a refreshing addition to meals.

Name: Garlic (Lehsun)
Detailed_Description: Garlic is a herb, best known for flavouring and seasoning of food and is widely used in various cuisines ranging from desi cuisines like Tadka Dal to dishes such as Garlic Bread. Garlic seems to be used in virtually all cuisines as a strong flavoring agent.

Name: Safal Sweet Corn (Frozen)
Detailed_Description: Healthy and nutritious, Safal Sweet Corn makes for a versatile kitchen ingredient. It can be grilled, steamed or boiled and served with seasoning. It is also used in the preparation of pizza, pasta, gravies, cakes, Pulao, custards, etc.

Name: Red Bell Pepper
Detailed_Description: Red bell peppers or red capsicum are commonly used in cooking due to their versatility and appealing taste. They can be eaten raw in salads, sliced as a snack, or cooked in various dishes such as stir-fries, fajitas, soups, and roasted vegetables.

Name: Green Peas (Matar)
Detailed_Description: These fresh tiny pods have a tender and a slightly sweet taste. Green Peas have a rich green colour and a starchy texture which makes it a perfect add-on to any dish. They are best paired with onions, potatoes for making yummy Indian delicacies such as kebabs and aromatic Pulao.

Name: Bottle Gourd (Lauki)
Detailed_Description: Bottle gourd is used most often in cooked applications and can be sautéed, fried, pickled or grilled. Bottle Gourd is used a lot in Indian preparations. With a short cooking time, it is often found in soups, stir fried, dal or simply served as a sabzi.

Name: Mint Leaves (Without Roots) (Pudina)
Detailed_Description: Mint Leaves cleaned and roots removed with only stem and leaves

Name: Curry Leaves (Kadi Patta)
Detailed_Description: Curry Leaves commonly called as Kadhi Patta, are highly aromatic and have a unique flavor with notes of citrus. They're used in cooking to add flavor to dishes, such as curries, rice dishes, and dals. Fresh or dried curry leaves are used whole, crushed, and chopped.

Name: Broccoli
Detailed_Description: Broccoli is a nutritious vegetable that belongs to the cruciferous family, along with cauliflower, cabbage, and kale. Known for its mild, slightly bitter flavor and crunchy texture. It can be eaten raw or cooked and is versatile in various dishes and salads.

Name: Safal Frozen Green Peas
Detailed_Description: Experience the amazing taste of green peas that can be enjoyed round-the-year. These Safal Frozen Green Peas are known for their superior quality. Sourced from the choicest farms and have been picked with great care. The taste is as good as fresh peas and will save you the work of shelling the peas. Your health is of top-priority; that is why these have been processed under hygienic conditions. Be it peas pulao, matar paneer, or aloo matar, your dishes will be lip-smackingly delicious with Safal Frozen Peas.

Detailed_Description: Cherry tomatoes add brightness and freshness to a variety of dishes,making them a delicious and colorful addition to meals. Enjoy cherry tomatoes raw in salads,pasta dishes,or as a flavorful topping for pizzas and bruschetta.

Detailed_Description: Enjoy the rich flavor of Small Purple Brinjal. Packed with antioxidants, vitamins, and fiber, it supports heart health and aids digestion. Perfect for grilling, roasting, or adding to curries, this versatile vegetable adds nutrition and taste to your meals.
